原句：Giving back to my community was truly a ______ (reward) experience.
你的答案：reward
正确答案：rewarding
错误原因：词性误用，修饰名词experience需要形容词，reward是名词，形容词形式为rewarding（有益的、收获满满的）。

1.
原题：According to the article, visitors should plan ahead during World Cup season because some public transportation ______.
A. stops running at night
B. becomes very expensive
C. does not run on weekends
D. does not always run on time
你的答案：B
正确答案：D
错误原因：原文说明世界杯客流大增，交通延误增多，因此需要提前规划，本质是公交不能总是准点运行；你错误理解了提前规划的原因，误以为是票价上涨。
2.
原题：According to the article, which of the following is NOT true about New York subway?
A. It is inexpensive.
B. It runs 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.
C. It is easy for first-time visitors to understand.
D. It runs mostly between the city’s northern and southern sides.
你的答案：A
正确答案：C
错误原因：题目要求选出错误表述，原文写地铁对新手来说confusing（令人困惑），并不容易理解；A 选项 “地铁价格低廉” 是原文正确信息，你选错了判断对象。

3.
原题：Ben arrived in New York around midnight and took a taxi to his hotel. The streets were empty. The distance from the airport to his hotel was 5.2 miles. How much did Ben need to pay for the taxi ride?
A. $15.50　B. $16.00　C. $16.50　D. $18.00
你的答案：A
正确答案：B
计价依据：起步价 $2.50 + 每 0.2 英里 $0.50 + 夜间附加费 $0.50，路面无拥堵，不加拥堵费
错误原因：没有逐条拆分收费项目，计算时遗漏 / 错加费用，最终总价计算错误。

4.
原题：This article would most likely appear in/on a ______.
A. local newspaper
B. travel guide
C. science magazine
D. sports website
你的答案：D
正确答案：B
错误原因：文章主要介绍纽约景点、各类出行交通方式，属于旅行指南；虽然提到世界杯，但核心内容是城市旅行出行，并非体育网站内容，文体判断失误。

原题：The new phone model is ______ the same as the old one, just with a better camera. (basic)
你的答案：based
正确答案：basically
错误原因：词性误用，此处需要副词修饰形容词same，basic 是形容词，副词形式为 basically（基本上），你错误写成了 based。

第 1 题
原题：Before his first marathon, the author felt ______.
A. confident because he had worked out for years
B. nervous about competing with others younger than him
C. calm because he knew the secret to running faster than others
D. uncertain about whether he could safely finish the whole race
你的答案：B
正确答案：D
错误原因：误解原文情绪描写，作者紧张并非因为和年轻人比拼，而是不确定自己能否顺利完赛。

第 4 题
原题：The underlined word “distract” in paragraph 4 most likely means “______.”
A. excite
B. encourage
C. take away attention
D. protect from harm
你的答案：B
正确答案：C
错误原因：词义理解错误，distract 意为 “转移注意力，分心”，不是鼓励（encourage）。

第 1 题
原题：______ she is from Gen Z, she has already achieved more than many athletes do in their entire careers.
你的答案：A. Because
正确答案：C. Although
错误原因：句子为让步关系，并非因果关系，要用 although（虽然）。

第 2 题
原题：She ______ reached 10th in the world rankings.
你的答案：A. quietly
正确答案：B. suddenly
错误原因：语境是 16 岁一举闯入世界前十，是 “突然” 达成，suddenly 符合文意。

第 6 题
原题：It is the highest ______ for active players.
你的答案：B. goal
正确答案：A. honour
错误原因：“Megastar” 是授予运动员的最高荣誉，并非目标。
